Exercise 8.1

Clean Model

# Clean up NHANES data table
NHANESclean <- 
  NHANES %>%
  filter(!is.na(SleepTrouble) & !is.na(Age) & !is.na(BMI) & !is.na(DaysPhysHlthBad))
NHANESclean

Null model

# Creating null model for SleepTrouble
mod_null <- tally(~ SleepTrouble, data = NHANESclean, format = "percent")
mod_null
SleepTrouble
      No      Yes 
74.58092 25.41908

** This model provides a baseline for the analysis of the SleepTrouble variable, as it says that we would by right around 74.6% of the time if we just assumed that someone did not have sleep trouble. **

# Creating logistic model for SleepTrouble
mod_logit <- glm(SleepTrouble ~ Age + BMI, data = NHANESclean, family = "binomial")
msummary(mod_logit)

Exercise 8.3

rr # Creating test and training scale n <- nrow(NHANESclean) test_idx <- sample.int(n, size = round(0.25 * n)) train <- NHANESclean[-test_idx, ]
nrow(train)

test <- NHANESclean[test_idx, ] nrow(test)

rr # Creating train and test null models train_mod_null <- tally(~ SleepTrouble, data = train, format = ) train_mod_null

test_mod_null <- tally(~ SleepTrouble, data = test, format = ) test_mod_null

** Higher accuracy for training data than test data. **

rr # Creating train and test logistic models train_mod_logit <- glm(SleepTrouble ~ Age + BMI, data = train, family = ) msummary(train_mod_logit)

test_mod_logit <- glm(SleepTrouble ~ Age + BMI, data = test, family = ) msummary(test_mod_logit)

rr # Confusion matrixes for train and test logistic models train_SleepTrouble_logitProb <- predict(mod_logit, newdata = train, type = ) train_SleepTrouble_logit <- ifelse(train_SleepTrouble_logitProb > 0.5, yes = , ) train_confusion <- tally(train_SleepTrouble_logit ~ SleepTrouble, data = train, format = ) train_confusion

test_SleepTrouble_logitProb <- predict(mod_logit, newdata = test, type = ) test_SleepTrouble_logit <- ifelse(test_SleepTrouble_logitProb > 0.5, yes = , ) test_confusion <- tally(test_SleepTrouble_logit ~ SleepTrouble, data = test, format = ) test_confusion

rr # Model accuaracies for train and test logistic model train_logit_acc <- sum(diag(train_confusion)) / nrow(train) * 100 train_logit_acc

test_logit_acc <- sum(diag(test_confusion)) / nrow(test) * 100 test_logit_acc

** Higher accuracy for traing data than testing data. **

rr # Decision trees for train and test train_mod_tree <- rpart(SleepTrouble ~ ., data = train) mod_tree

test_mod_tree <- rpart(SleepTrouble ~ ., data = test) mod_tree

rr # Plots for train and test decision tree plot(as.party(train_mod_tree))

plot(as.party(test_mod_tree))

rr # Branching and pruning for train and test decision trees printcp(train_mod_tree)

printcp(test_mod_tree)

rr # Confusion matrixes for train and test decision tree train_NC_tree <- train %>% mutate(train_SleepTrouble_dtree = predict(train_mod_tree, type = )) train_confusion <- tally(train_SleepTrouble_dtree ~ SleepTrouble, data = train_NC_tree, format = ) train_confusion

test_NC_tree <- test %>% mutate(test_SleepTrouble_dtree = predict(test_mod_tree, type = )) test_confusion <- tally(test_SleepTrouble_dtree ~ SleepTrouble, data = test_NC_tree, format = ) test_confusion

rr # Model accuaracies for train and test decision trees train_dtree_acc <- sum(diag(train_confusion)) / nrow(train) * 100 train_dtree_acc

test_dtree_acc <- sum(diag(test_confusion)) / nrow(test) * 100 test_dtree_acc

** Higher accuracy for test data than training data. **

rr # Creating random forest train_mod_forest <- randomForest(SleepTrouble ~ Age + BMI, data = train, ntree = 2000, mtry = 2) train_mod_forest

test_mod_forest <- randomForest(SleepTrouble ~ Age + BMI, data = test, ntree = 2000, mtry = 2) test_mod_forest

rr # Model accuracy for random forest train_rf_acc <- sum(diag(train_mod_forest$confusion)) / nrow(train) * 100 train_rf_acc

test_rf_acc <- sum(diag(test_mod_forest$confusion)) / nrow(test) * 100 test_rf_acc

** Higher accuracy for traing data than testing data. **

rr # Creating neural network train_mod_nnet <- nnet(SleepTrouble ~ Age + BMI, data = train, size = 3)

test_mod_nnet <- nnet(SleepTrouble ~ Age + BMI, data = test, size = 3)

rr # Confusion matrix for nueral network train_SleepTrouble_nn <- predict(train_mod_nnet, newdata = train, type = ) train_confusion <- tally(train_SleepTrouble_nn ~ SleepTrouble, data = train, format = ) train_confusion

test_SleepTrouble_nn <- predict(test_mod_nnet, newdata = test, type = ) test_confusion <- tally(test_SleepTrouble_nn ~ SleepTrouble, data = test, format = ) test_confusion

rr # Model accuracy for neural network train_nnet_acc <- sum(diag(train_confusion)) / nrow(train) * 100 train_nnet_acc

test_nnet_acc <- sum(diag(test_confusion)) / nrow(test) * 100 test_nnet_acc

** Higher accuracy for test data than training data. **

rr # Creating Naive Bayes/confusion matrix for Naive Bayes train_mod_nb <- naiveBayes(SleepTrouble ~ Age + BMI, data = train) train_SleepTrouble_nb <- predict(train_mod_nb, newdata = train) train_confusion <- tally(train_SleepTrouble_nb ~ SleepTrouble, data = train, format = ) train_confusion

test_mod_nb <- naiveBayes(SleepTrouble ~ Age + BMI, data = test) test_SleepTrouble_nb <- predict(test_mod_nb, newdata = test) test_confusion <- tally(test_SleepTrouble_nb ~ SleepTrouble, data = test, format = ) test_confusion

rr # Model accuracy for Naive Bayes train_nb_acc <- sum(diag(train_confusion)) / nrow(train) * 100 train_nb_acc

test_nb_acc <- sum(diag(test_confusion)) / nrow(test) * 100 test_nb_acc

** Higher accuracy for test data than training data. **

rr # Creating KNN train_SleepTrouble_quant <- train %>% select(Age, BMI)

train_SleepTrouble_knn <- knn(train = train_SleepTrouble_quant, test = train_SleepTrouble_quant, cl = train$SleepTrouble, k = 5)

train_confusion <- tally(train_SleepTrouble_knn ~ SleepTrouble, data = train, format = ) train_confusion

test_SleepTrouble_quant <- test %>% select(Age, BMI)

test_SleepTrouble_knn <- knn(train = test_SleepTrouble_quant, test = test_SleepTrouble_quant, cl = test$SleepTrouble, k = 5)

test_confusion <- tally(test_SleepTrouble_knn ~ SleepTrouble, data = test, format = ) test_confusion

rr # Model accuracy for KNN train_knn_acc <- sum(diag(train_confusion)) / nrow(train) * 100 train_knn_acc

test_knn_acc <- sum(diag(test_confusion)) / nrow(test) * 100 test_knn_acc

** Higher accuracy for training data than test data. **

Ensemble Assignment

rr # Train Model vote <- 3 train_ensemble <- ifelse((train_SleepTrouble_knn == ) + (train_SleepTrouble_nn == ) + (train_mod_nb == ) + (train_mod_logit == ) + (train_mod_forest$predicted == ) >= vote, , ) train_confusion <- tally(train_ensemble ~ SleepTrouble, data = train, format = ) train_confusion

train_ens_acc <- sum(diag(train_confusion)) / nrow(train) * 100 train_ens_acc

rr # Test Model vote <- 3 test_ensemble <- ifelse((test_SleepTrouble_knn == ) + (test_SleepTrouble_nn == ) + (test_mod_nb == ) + (test_mod_logit == ) + (test_mod_forest$predicted == ) >= vote, , ) test_confusion <- tally(test_ensemble ~ SleepTrouble, data = test, format = ) test_confusion

test_ens_acc <- sum(diag(test_confusion)) / nrow(test) * 100 test_ens_acc

** The train ensemble is the more accurate model than the test ensemble. **
